Setup ELK in Mac
1. Install Elasticsearch
	$brew install elasticsearch

2. Install Logstash
	$brew install logstash

3. Install Kibana
	$brew install kibana

4. Create a directory to save all the config files for logstash
	$mkdir /usr/local/Cellular/logstash/1.5.4/conf

6. Create a basic config(say logstash_test.conf) filter inside conf directory.
	$cd /usr/local/Cellular/logstash/1.5.4/conf
	$nano logstash_test.conf
	
	The content of file looklike:
	input {
    file {
    path => "Desktop/logfile.txt"
    start_position => "beginning"
    sincedb_path => "/dev/null"
    }
    }
	output {
	elasticsearch { host => localhost protocol => "http"}
	stdout { codec=> rubydebug }
	}



7. Run elasticsearch
	$cd /usr/local/Cellar/elasticsearch/1.7.1/bin/
	$elasticsearch

8. Go to your web browser and type localhost:9200 and verify elasticsearch is running

9. Open a new terminal tab & run logstash
	$cd cd /usr/local/Cellar/logstash/1.5.4/conf/
	$logstash agent -f logstash_test.conf --debug

10. Run kibana from location of kibana
	$cd /usr/local/Cellar/kibana/4.1.1/bin
	$kibana

11. Go to your web browser and type localhost:5601 and verify kibana is running

12. Create a index pattern in kibana interface

13. Go to discover tab choose your time range to see the logs in Kibana
